   <mods:abstract>Is sorry to hear of John Jay's poor health. The sheep have been procured
            from a neighbor and are being shipped to his son. Was to have sent some sheep and
            ploughs to England and procured letters from the British Ministry to the Board of Trade,
            but the "mulish scariness" of the ship owner prevented their being sent. Peters'
            neighbor is a Democrat but is much attached to John Jay, the reason being that though
            Jay had been much abused, his character was one which would "bear great Deductions, and
            still remain more perfect than that of most men." Discourse on Merino sheep and the
            manufacture of wool. Nothing more heard on the subject in which Dr. M. is mentioned. Did
            not communicate John Jay's additional corrections of the interpretation of his first
            letter since it would "keep alive a Subject best put at rest." Agricultural
            news.</mods:abstract>
